The III International Student Film Festival "Bastau" was launched in Almaty.
This year's festival will be chaired by Iraqi Kvirikadze, a well-known filmmaker, screenwriter and teacher.
The jury includes Silvan Kutandin ("Letter to Stein"), Russian actress Elvira Bolgová ("My Armenian Wedding", "Ogei Daughter"), Kyrgyz director Temirbek Birnazaraov and Kazakh writer Sabit Kurmanbekov.
Along with the main jury, the jury is composed of young cinematographers-students, as is the tradition in the "Bastauda" year.
This year's student jury includes students from Spain, Belarus, Kazakhstan, Kyrgyzstan, Russia.
The Spanish director Яго Mateo Velasko, who won the "Bastava" two years ago, is now the chairman of the jury that evaluates the works of talented students.
