The fact that the festival is international is a good thing for students, and we get a little insight into what the future of cinema will be.
Of course, there's the Oscars, there's the Cannes Film Festival, but you can't go there right away, so it's good to have a ladder like "The Beginning" that leads to the big contests.
The most important thing is literacy, a new worldview, we want to give young talented people access to the world of big festivals", says Mateo Velasko.
The festival was attended by the Dean of the Faculty of Film Production of Korea University of Media Arts Kim En-Doo, the sound director of Mosfilm Marina Nigmatullina and the cinematographer, the lecturer of the Karpenko-Karogo University of Ukraine Evgeny Filippov.
The jury and guests of the festival will have creative meetings and master classes with students of Almaty, specialists in cinema.
