The international film festival is an important venue for young people.
The student should see from the very first job what competition is, not only what his peers are shooting, but also how their peers in other countries are looking for it.
It's not just about the film, it's about the interaction with the filmmakers, the exchange of ideas.
"Starting" is a crucial step in establishing creative communication.
Despite the complexities, the difficulty of stepping into the big cinematography, cinema has evolved.
Film festivals are essential for this purpose.
Cinema is a collective work, international cinema is universal, and we contribute to its development.
We are not just watching the film here, we are learning how to make it, says the president of the festival Sergey Azimov.
