The rules of the fight against "black archaeology" will be approved.
After the "black archaeologists", the monuments are left in the open and destroyed.
This was stated by Minister of Culture and Sports Aristanbek Mukhamediuly during the presentation of the draft law "On protection and use of historical and cultural heritage objects" in the Majilis.
The issue of regulating archaeological and restoration works on objects of historical and cultural heritage requires a review.
It is no secret that our unique monuments or unstudied objects are often subjected to search and excavation by "black archaeologists", after which the monuments are left in an open state and partially or completely destroyed.
In addition, the intensive construction works carried out in the adjacent areas of historical and cultural heritage objects have significant effects on the historical integrity and preservation of historical and cultural monuments and have negative consequences.
In general, there is a need to strengthen the legal sphere, which requires specific regulation and creation of favorable conditions for the protection and use of historical and cultural heritage objects , - the Minister noted.
According to him, in this regard, it is considered to establish the procedure for identification and accounting of objects of historical and cultural heritage at the legislative level, as well as monitoring their condition, to introduce new mechanisms for the preservation and use of objects of historical and cultural heritage in their final historical appearance.
In addition, it is proposed to establish rules and conditions for conducting archaeological works and combating "black archaeology", regulate the legal regime of land use in protected areas, construction of historical and cultural monuments, define the legal regime of use of natural landscape areas.
The draft law was drafted with the help of international experience.
For example, Russian legislation has introduced measures to combat illegal archaeological excavations, the confiscation of archaeological objects, the avoidance of the sale of artifacts to the state, and so on.
So, criminal responsibility is provided.
In Italy, there are obligations for private collectors at the legislative level.
According to them, it is planned to create and periodically update lists of cultural and art objects of historical and artistic interest and located in private property.
In addition , the objects in the property of the owners of these objects are subject to state protection , regardless of their nationality , - said A.Muhamedievich.
The festival "Kavsi Qazaq Eri" will be held in Astana and will be attended by compatriots from 10 countries.
The international festival of art "Kavli Kazakhli" will be held in the capital with the participation of foreign compatriots , the correspondent of KazInfo reports .
The festival will be attended by about 50 artists from 10 countries.
35 of them are from abroad, the rest are from our country.
Our compatriots from France, Afghanistan, Turkey, Iran and other countries are visiting the garden.
The competition will be held in three directions: traditional craft competition, the competition of the artists and the chorus.
This festival is a significant event that is held every year.
The aim is to bring together our compatriots living abroad and to celebrate our national art together.
We decided to hold the art competition in the capital city.
Next year, we will hold regional festivals in all regions of the country and select the best ones.
We plan to organize a large-scale festival in Astana at the end of the year , - said the head of the Astana and Akmola regional branch of the World Kazakh Association Karlyagash Bekpatshavna .
According to the organizers, the art event is important for strengthening relations with compatriots abroad.
And the exception this year is that it is held in Astana for the first time.
The total prize fund of the international art competition is about 3 million tenge .
The event will be held on November 7 at the Palace of Peace and Reconciliation, organized by the World Kazakh Association and the Foundation "Otanadas".
The sponsor is the Ministry of Community Development .
